KANO – Senator Rabiu Musa Kwankwaso, former two-term governor of Kano state on Tuesday officially exited the Peoples Democratic party in a signed letter sent to his ward chairman. Kwankwaso was first elected as governor of Kano State on the platform of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) in 1999, lost reelection in 2003, but staged a comeback in 2011 on the political party. He dumped the party and joined the change agenda of All Progressives Congress in 2014, but returned to PDP in 2017 over irreconcilable differences with APC. Details soon…